For in this same year, in the month of December, five days after Christmas‚ the enemy of man’s peace stirred up our citizens to such miser-able discord that in the midst of our streets and places they have fallen upon one another with arms in hand : after which followed a great many murderS, woundings, burningS, and plunderings. In 1298, at the age of seventy, the apostle of con- ciliation passed over to the world of peace unalloyed. In his last dispositions he bequeathed the little he possessed to the poor of Genoa: he provided that his body should be laid without pomp in the Dominican cloister whose humble and studious shades he had quitted with reluctance.
